This paper is about recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper specifically focuses on the use of deep neural networks for recommendation, which is a popular topic in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) community. The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques, as it deals with modeling user-item interactions and latent features.
